Nehawu has threatened a massive strike after the national lockdown. The union isn't happy with government's failure to implement a 2018 wage increase that would have taken effect on Wednesday. Courtesy #DStv403 The union's Deputy General Secretary, December Mavuso speaks to eNCA JOHANNESBURG - Trade union Nehawu said government doesn't care about the safety of health workers in their fight against COVID-19. The union is demanding they be provided with personal protective equipment. READ: Nehawu calls for protection for workers from COVID-19 It said there has been no response from the Health Department, and it's now taking its fight to court. Nehawu is filing urgent court papers to compel the government to provide its members with proper protective gear in hospitals. READ: Nehawu threatens court action over protective gear Nehawu spokesperson Ayanda Zulu said the union supports the interventions suggested by the government, but their members must be adequately supplied with equipment to fight against the spread of COVID-19. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.